						<summary>

						<p>On the north wall of the Veṅkaṭēśa-perumāḷ temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Rājakēsarivarman: Year 37.</hi></p>						

						<p>This fragmentary inscription in characters of about the 12th century, seems to have recorded a grant of gold and lands to god Āḷuḍaiyār ••••• at Koḻumam in Karaivaḻi-nāḍu by the <hi rend="italic">Sabhā</hi> of a chaturvēdimaṅgalam (name lost), and mentions Adhirādarāja-vāykkāl. </p>						

						</summary>
